demie. Gestützt auf eingehende Quellenstudien, wirft der Band so ein neues Licht auf die Entwicklung des Schweizer Kunstschaffens.  aDuring the 19th century the Swiss art world was characterized by intense interaction with other countries. The author examines these interrelations to develop a new conception of Swiss art, using the example of the Swiss student of David, Hans Jakob Oeri, to reveal the ties between art, governmental affairs, artistic mobility, and artistic reception. The work thus presents for the first time a history of the Swiss Academy of Fine Arts.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aArt, Moderny19th centuryxHistory. 7aART / Individual Artists / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1z978311076251808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z97831107009850 cEPUBz97831103825320 cprintz978311033998740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034140940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110341409423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110341409/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-076251-8  DG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK